name: Identifiable Name or Title
description: Full name, title or identifiable part of an individual. (e.g., first name, last name, user name, organization name).

name: Identification TimeDate
description: Dates or times that are used to identify or verify a person, such as birth dates, issue dates on documents, or timestamps related to identity records.
examples: In a virtual meetup scheduled for 13:23:10 in the <LOCATION> on 2055-10-16T00:00:00

name: Identification Number
description: Numbers assigned to individuals for identification, such as Social Security Numbers or National ID.

name: Phone Number
description: Phone numbers that can identify or contact an individual.

name: Credential Information
description: Phone numbers that can identify or contact an individual.

name: Location Data

example: I live at 123 Baker Street, London.

name: Online Identifier
description: Includes IP addresses, cookies, or other digital identifiers.

name: Email Address
description: An email that can be used to identify or contact a person.

name: Geopolitical Entities
description: Information indicating membership in a labor union.
example: He joined the workers' union last year.
considered the father of Soviet socialist realism

name: Statistical Data
description: Information that can be used to identify a person based on statistical analysis, such as demographic data.
example: company said profit fell 49% to $23.5 million from $46 million

name: Biometric Data
description: Data like fingerprints, facial recognition, or retina scans.
example: His phone unlocks with a fingerprint scan.

name: Genetic Data
description: Data concerning inherited or acquired genetic characteristics.
example: The DNA test revealed a rare gene mutation.

name: Health Data
description: Any information about physical or mental health conditions.
example: She was diagnosed with diabetes last year.

name: Racial or Ethnic Origin
description: Information that reveals a person's race or ethnicity.
classification_hint: Look for descriptors like 'Asian Caucasian African', etc.

name: Political Opinions
description: Statements or affiliations related to politics or parties.
classification_hint: Look for mentions of political views, parties, or ideology.
example: She is a member of the Green Party.

name: Religious or Philosophical Beliefs
description: Information about personal beliefs or religious affiliations.
classification_hint: Look for words like 'Christian Muslim atheist believe in'.

name: Sex Life or Sexual Orientation
description: Information about a person's sexual orientation or activities.
classification_hint: Look for terms like 'gay straight bisexual', or explicit sexual references.
example: He came out as gay in college.
students with different needs, including Feminine and M

name: Criminal Convictions
description: Data about criminal history or offenses.
classification_hint: Look for phrases like 'convicted of arrested for', or 'criminal record'.
example: He was convicted of theft in 2018.
